    "fullName": "Hospital Anxiety and Depression Scale",
    "description": "The HADS is a 14-item self-report scale designed to detect anxiety and depression in medical outpatient settings. It avoids somatic symptoms that might be confused with physical illness, making it particularly suitable for hospital patients.",
